    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Ninjutsu </p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 5 (Spell Level 3)</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 6</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 18 | <b>Successes:</b> 2</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 6 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 18</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> C, F</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>You form opposite elemental energies in both your hands and fire them in a ray, dealing 2d6 cold and 2d6 fire damage, and having a random additional effect (roll a d6):<br><br>- 1 (Electric Release): The target is @Condition[paralyzed;duration=1]{paralyzed} for 1 round (Fortitude negates)<br>- 2 (Violent Explosion): The effect becomes a 5 ft Burst (it is no longer a ray), and allows a Reflex save for half damage.<br>- 3 (Cold Snap):  Frost creeps up the target's legs, entangling it for 1d4 rounds.<br>- 4 (Wind Shock): The target falls @Condition[prone]{prone} (Reflex negates).<br>- 5 (Bright Flash): The target becomes @Condition[blind]{blinded} for 1d3 rounds (Fortitude negates).<br>- 6 (Dark Matter): The ray deals 1d6 bonus force damage.</p>\n\n\n<p><b>Mastery:</b> The fifth step allows you to reroll the random effect once per use of the technique.</p>\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
